Metaverse:  Rosie's Pixel Garden, of 3.City


"Her green eyes were emeralds as the hologram materialized at the entrance.  The greeting program began guiding the latest visitors into the west botanical wings, as she poured a glass of Veuve Clicquot La Grande Dame Rose, 1990.  She opened the blinds with the eastern view of the neighboring building as she turned the volume up on her favorite sound.  She sat in her chair as a tear began to form. One after another, the tears fell on her buttermilk cheeks.  Tears of happiness, almost as if each moment of pain she experienced flowed though her eyes and nourished the plant on the stand next to her.  Rosie's mood began to change, and with it so did the rooms lighting.  She took a sip as her communicator notified her that her guests have arrived."
